TomKat Ranch: Birds

Since 2010, Point Blue Conservation Science has conducted 895 bird surveys across TomKat Ranch during May and June and detected a total of 91 bird species.

Species richness is concentrated in riparian areas

In 2015, we consistently detected more species per survey at riparian points along Honsinger Creek than grassland points.

Click on any of the points to learn more.


Back to top



No trend in species richness over time

Since 2010, species richness has been consistently higher at riparian points than grassland points.

Glossary


Riparian: The interface between land and a river or stream. Riparian vegetation provides important wildlife habitat, reduces soil erosion, and shades streams. We considered all survey points along Honsinger Creek to be riparian points.


Grassland: We considered all survey points with at least 50% of the area within 100m covered by grass, hay, or pasture to be grassland points, excluding points with >50% shrubs or trees.
